    • Method Detail

      • makeCaptureSettings

        static <T extends MakesCapturesOnFinishing> void makeCaptureSettings​(T toBeSetUp)
        It is possible to annotate any subclass of MakesCapturesOnFinishing by MakeImageCapturesOnFinishing, MakeFileCapturesOnFinishing, MakeStringCapturesOnFinishing and MakeCaptureOnFinishing to define captures to be made by Captor.getData(java.lang.Object) after invocation of Consumer.accept(Object) or Function.apply(Object) on built resulted Consumer/ Function. This method makes the setting up according to annotations used by a class of the object/superclasses.
        Type Parameters:
        T - is a type of MakesCapturesOnFinishing
        Parameters:
        toBeSetUp - an instance of MakesCapturesOnFinishing to be tuned.

      • makeImageCaptureOnFinish

        T makeImageCaptureOnFinish()
        Marks that it is needed to produce a BufferedImage after invocation of Consumer.accept(Object) or Function.apply(Object) on built resulted Consumer/Function. This image is produced by Captor.getData(java.lang.Object)

        NOTE 1

        This image is produced if there is any subclass of ImageCaptor or Captor that may produce a BufferedImage.

        NOTE 2

        A subclass of ImageCaptor or Captor should be able to handle input values of Consumer.accept(Object) and/or resulted values of Function.apply(Object).
        Returns:
        self-reference
